  "prompt": "U.S. Immigration: If a US B1 visa is rejected, how many days should I wait to reapply to avoid rejection?",
  "response": "There's no mandatory waiting period for reapplying after a B1 visa rejection. However, it's recommended to:\n\n1. Wait at least 3-6 months\n2. Address the specific reasons for the previous rejection\n3. Gather stronger supporting documents\n4. Demonstrate significant changes in your circumstances\n5. Be prepared to clearly explain your travel intentions\n\nThe key is to improve your application by providing more convincing evidence of:\n- Strong ties to your home country\n- Sufficient financial resources\n- Clear purpose of visit\n- Intent to return after temporary stay\n\nEach application is evaluated individually, so focus on strengthening your overall application rather than just waiting a specific number of days.",
